Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Campus Library Coordinator Penticton , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Campus Library CoordinatorCompetition Number:C002542Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:PentictonYour Opportunity:Under the limited supervision of the Campus Librarian, the Campus Library Coordinator is responsible for the day-to-day operation of the public area of the Campus Library; provides leadership and direction to the Circulation team to ensure high quality service delivery; develops, recommends and implements policies and procedures; works with the Campus Librarian and other departments to ensure the smooth operation of the campus library; assists library users with library processes and helps defuse and resolve difficult interactions with library users. The Campus Library Coordinator coordinates training and scheduling of support staff, student library pages, and student IT lab monitors.Education and Experience:Completion of a 2-year Library Technician Diploma and an additional 2 years academic post-secondary education are required. A minimum of 4 years’ experience in an academic library is required.Functions and Duties:Coordinates work schedules for support staff and student employees to meet Library operating requirements and service standardsEstablishes work standards and monitors and assesses work output for Library public services areas and responds to and provides direction on issues that require immediate supervisory attentio