ponsible for coordinating statistics and reports for reference, user education and other public servicesAssists library users, including students, employees and the general public, by telephone, electronically and face-to-face; handles queries in a sensitive and timely manner and refers to the Campus Librarian, other OC departments, or other resources as appropriateHelps library users to locate materials, search for information using the online catalogue, research databases, and web search engines, properly cite sources, use library equipment including microfilm/fiche readers, photocopiers and printers and with routine productivity software and institutional computer accountsCoordinates and assists with operational activities in public services including answering user questions and referring to appropriate resources, opening and closing library facilities as necessary, borrower services activities related to library cards, circulating library materials, intercampus requests; monitors the delivery processes and services supporting circulation; maintains the library reserves systemCarries out collection management activities such as collection inventory and the resolution of periodical holdings discrepancies; identifies and reviews cataloguing, processing and other anomalies; reports discrepanciesEnsures appropriate maintenance of Library public service area facilities, technology and equipment (i.e. laptops, photocopiers, computers) by reporting issues, submitting work requests, and coordinating with the appropriate departmentAccesses the student registration system to confirm student course registration or as otherwise requiredPerforms other duties as assigned.Skills and Abilities:Knowledge of automated library systemsProficiency with MS Office programs, particularly Word and ExcelTechnical aptitude for learning new systems and software and propensity for life-long learning to ensure technical currencyAbility to work effectively with limited supervisionAbility to p